I'm just going to stick with Nagoya as it's cheaper with better service.

EDIT 7/29/17:  After coming here many times over the past year, it has become apparent that some time in the past months the waitstaff were completely replaced.  The previous staff were experienced and friendly.  The service is still good.  Tenzan is a Japanese restaurant with an inviting atmosphere, a gem to be found in the area.  With dependable, quality food, approachable customer service, and a clean and high-quality environment, it is definitely a league higher than the other restaurants around it.  Because of this, Tenzan quickly became a favorite of mine when I moved here.  The food is well-made and tasty.  I love the ginger-carrot dressing salad.  The katsu is crispy and goes great with their white rice.  Compared to the other Japanese restaurants in the area, Tenzan feels much more authentic.  P.S. If you are hoping to sit in their sliding door booths, you should make a reservation beforehand.
